	<h1 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;text-align: center;padding: 5px;">Bf Solution Group</h1>
	<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;text-align: center;padding: 10px;font-weight: 300;">AGREEMENT ON LEGAL SERVICES GENERAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS</h3>
	<p>An Agreement is regarded as concluded if it is in a format which is also reproducible in writing and I the volume, scope and terms of provision of legal services is agreed to by email signing a formal client agreement. Oral client agreements may be entered into only for a one-time purpose or for provision of legal services in respect of a clearly defined assignment, and when possible, these oral agreements should be confirmed by e-mail.</p>
	<p>Legal services will be provided on behalf of <strong>Bf Solutions Group</strong> only by members of the Bar Association of the jurisdiction where <strong>Bf Solutions Group</strong> is established i.e., attorneys, senior assistant attorneys and assistant attorneys respectively, depending upon each
jurisdiction Attorneys and senior assistant attorneys provides legal services independently, while assistant attorneys provide legal services under the supervision of an attorney pursuant to the provisions of the Local Bar Association attorneys may engage other employees working for the <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> in provision of legal services.</p>
<p>Such employees cannot independently provide legal services to a client on behalf of <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong>, but they assist the attorneys who engage them in provision of legal services under the supervision of, and on the responsibility of those attorneys.</p>
<p>Only those attorneys and employees who are actually engaged in provision of services to the Client are considered as engaged. <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> and its attorneys will represent and defend the victims involved in the online trading investment scheme across disputes, negotiations and proceedings out of court and in court, in arbitration tribunals and elsewhere.</p>
<p>Limitations on the right of representation are agreed to in writing or in a formatre producible in writing. In particular assignments, e.g., court representations, the Client will provide a separate power of attorney for performing the assignments agreed to in the First Part of the Agreement.</p>
<p>On request the Client will promptly deliver documents positions and perform other acts necessary for timely performance of the assignment. Unless agreed with the Client in writing or in a format reproducible in writing, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> does not undertake to amend or update any information, opinions or documents provided to or prepared for the Client after performance of an assignment due to amendments to or revocation of legal acts.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 50%;">PROVISION OF LEGAL SERVICES:</h3>
<p>This outset indicates the provision of legal services, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> agrees with the Client on the scope of work to be performed as legal services over the cause of the case</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 40%;">SCOPE OF SERVICES :</h3>
<p>The Client (__*name_*____) has engaged <strong>Bf Solutions Group</strong> in connection with fraud case involving the online trading investment scheme</p>
<p>Bf Solutions Group representation is in connection with the indicated matter only, unless agreed otherwise in a signed writing. The Client undertakes to provide <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> all relevant information and documents concerning the assignment and to keeping <strong>Bf solution Group</strong> informed of facts that change or may be anticipated to change.</p>
<p>Scope of Services conducted by <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> to victims of the online trading scheme</p>
<ul>
	<li>Consultation</li>
	<li>Document Review</li>
	<li>Document Preparation</li>
	<li>Negotiation, arbitartion & Representation on behalf of the client in all forms of administrative or legislative hearings</li>
</ul>
<p>The Client undertakes to accept the assignment carried out by the attorneys and employees of <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> notify <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> regarding any amendments required. If the Client fails to deliver such notification to <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> the legal services shall be considered to have been accepted by the Client regardless of the outcome.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 45%;">FEES, COST & PAYMENTS:</h3>
<p>Fees and Costs Client will be responsible for all costs however in some cases <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may advance such costs. As used herein, the term “Costs,” includes, but is not limited to, filing fees, filing boxes and supplies, copying costs, deposition costs, computerized research costs, outsourced document scanning/coding/indexing costs, travel expenses, expert fees, court costs, postage expenses, witness fees, and reasonable interest paid by <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> to third-party lenders to cover any cost advances. Unless agreed otherwise, the Client pays <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> for legal services.</p>
<p>The amount of the fee for legal services requested by the Client is calculated on the basis of, but not limited to the following criteria:</p>
<ol type="i">
	<li>the time spent in fulfilling the assignment;</li>
	<li>the qualifications and experience of the attorney or employee performing the assignment, and the resources required for fulfilling the assignment;</li>
	<li>the business interest involved;</li>
	<li>the risks assumed (if any) in fulfilling the assignment; and</li>
	<li>the time constraints for fulfilling the assignment.</li>
</ol>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 30%;">EXTRA COSTS:</h3>
<p><strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may incur various costs and expenses in performing legal services under this agreement.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 40%;">Not a Contingent Fees:</h3>
<p>Client’s obligation to pay Fees and Costs is not contingent on the outcome of the Matter and must be paid by Client irrespective of the results obtained</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 60%;">Preparation of Documents to Transfer Assets:</h3>
<p>The fixed fee rate does not include time spent and costs incurred in the preparation and handling of any transfers of assets to Client. If Client wishes Law Firm to provide additional services relating to the transferring of assets, such additional services will be billed according to the Rate Schedule attached hereto</p>
<p>The amount of fees is determined irrespective of whether those fees will be reimbursed to the Client as cover for legal expenses or under an insurance policy acquired for any other reason, or whether, in a given dispute, the losing party is obliged to pay the costs
of the opposing party.<strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> will issue an invoice either directly to the Client or to a third person designated by the client If the third party designated by the Client fails to pay an invoice by the due date of payment, <strong>Bf Solution group</strong> may readdress the invoice in the name of the Client, and the Client shall pay the invoice by the due date of payment indicated in the invoice.</p>
<p>Fee estimates are always indicative and are based on information available to <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> at the time the estimate is given Unless agreed otherwise, fee estimates cannot be regarded as fixed quotes. Unless otherwise instructed by the Client, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may take such action as it considers necessary or advisable in order to carry out an assignment, and incur reasonable out-of-pocket expenses on the Client’s behalf.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 25%;">BILING:</h3>
<p><strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> will send Client monthly statements indicating attorneys' fees and costs incurred and their basis, and any current balance owed. invoices on a monthly basis, unless otherwise agreed in writing.</p>
<p>The term of payment of an invoice is 10 calendar days. The Client will reimburse <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> all additional expenses incurred in relation to the collection of any amounts not paid by the due date of payment by the Client.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 45%;">DELINQUENT ACCOUNTS:</h3>
<p>In the event that the Client does not pay his or her account in full when it becomes due, The Client agrees to pay all costs of collection plus a service charge on any delinquent balance at the rate of of 3% on the overdue amount for each calendar day of delay, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> will suspend provision of legal services, and withhold documents prepared for the Client’s assignment until full payment by the Client of amounts overdue.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 48%;">DOCUMENT / DATA RETENTION:</h3>
<p><strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> collects, stores, uses and processes personal data about the Client and the persons directly related to it. It is <strong>Bf Solutions Group</strong> policy to retain Client's file in its storage facility for a period of not more than seven (7) years. Thereafter, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> will ultimately destroy all files, documents, records, and writings related to each engagement for which <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> has been retained without notifying Client of the destruction of these items. To be certain that <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> has not retained any material that the Client may need or desire, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> will return to Client original documents which the Client has made available to <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> on request by the Client instructing Bf Solution Group in writing within thirty (30) days after <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> mails the Client a letter informing the Client that <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> has completed the services agreed to be provided under this agreement.</p>
<p>For the purposes of fulfilment of the Client’s assignment <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> will process the personal data of the Client and the persons directly related to it (e.g. employees and/or representatives) in the capacity as a personal data processor in accordance with laws and regulations governing personal data protection. The Client must inform <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> on security measures it requires for the protection of persona data processing. If the Client has not separately informed <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> on such security measures, the Client hereby agrees that the security measures taken by <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> correspond to the requirements of the Client and applicable law.</p>
<p>If necessary for the provision of legal services, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may process the personal data of another person or the Client obtained on the basis of the Agreement or by law, including sensitive personal data, without the consent of those persons.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 22%;">NOTICES:</h3>
<p>All notices, request, demand and other communications between the parties under this Agreement shall be made in writing or the preferred contact method indicated by the client.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 20%;">CLAIMS:</h3>
<p>Over the cause of <strong>Bf solution Group</strong> rending legal service to a client If a legal service is not in conformity with the terms of the Agreement, the Client may:
</p>
<ol type="i">
	<li>require performance of the obligation;</li>
	<li>withhold performance of an obligation which is due from the Client;</li>
	<li>demand compensation for damage;</li>
	<li>withdraw from or cancel the Agreement;</li>
	<li>require a reduction of the fees;</li>
	<li>in the case of a delay in performance of a monetary obligation, demand payment of default interest</li>
</ol>
<p>The Client who has a complaint or claim regarding the activities of an attorney or employee of <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> shall submit a complaint to <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> in a format reproducible in writing. The complaint must clearly set out a description of the Client’s rights that have been violated, and the circumstances of the violation.</p>
<p>Any existing evidence regarding violation of the Client’s rights must be appended to the complaint all claims for damages must be presented to <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> in writing. The Client shall be required to file a claim for damages during 12 months from the moment of receiving the legal service from <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> or from the moment when the assignment or a substantial part of it can reasonably be considered to have been completed, whichever occurs first.</p>
<p>If the Client’s claim against <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> is based on a claim by a third party (including the public authorities) against the Client, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may respond to and settle the claim or make an agreement on the Client’s behalf with the party filing the claim, provided that <strong>Bf solution Group</strong> indemnifies the Client for any direct damage related to it.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 40%;">CONFLICT OF INTEREST:</h3>
<p>Before accepting an assignment, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> always conducts an internal conflict-of-interest check to verify before <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> accepts the assignment. Notwithstanding such checks, circumstances may arise that prevent <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> from acting for the Client in an existing ongoing or future matter.</p>
<p>In these situations, the rules of professional conduct regulating conflicts of interest apply, and <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may terminate the Agreement. In addition, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> retains the rights to render legal assistance to other persons and execute assignments not connected to the Client’s assignment, including providing of services to persons operating in the same field as the Client or who might potentially have interests opposite of the ones of the Client.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 60%;">SEVERANCE OF RELATIONSHIP BY CLIENT:</h3>
<p>Client may discharge <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> at any time by written notice effective when received by <strong>bf solution Group</strong>. <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may terminate this Agreement at any time by serving a 14-day prior written notice to the Client before the termination date, unilaterally in cases, where <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> has a substantial reason, provided that such termination does not contradict rules of professional conduct and that the Client interests are duly respected. <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may terminate fulfilment of an assignment with an immediate effect (upon inform the Client thereof) provided that such termination does not contradict rules of professional conduct if the Client fails to pay an invoice for legal services when due.</p>
<p>Unless specifically agreed by <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> and Client, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> will provide no further services and advance no further costs on Client's behalf after receipt of the notice unless Law Firm is required by ethical or legal reasons to continue representing Client.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 48%;">WITHDRAWAL OF LAW FIRM:</h3>
<p><strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may withdraw its legal services at any time indicated below are a list of the circumstances under which the withdrawal may take place</p>
<ol type="a">
	<li>Client consents to withdrawal</li>
	<li> Client's conduct renders it unreasonably difficult for <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> to carry out the employment effectively</li>
	<li>Client fails to pay attorneys' fees or costs as required by his or her agreement with <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong></li>
</ol>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 48%;">DISCLAIMER OF GUARANTY:</h3>
<p><strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may express an opinion about possible results regarding the outcome of the Client's matter, although Bf Solution Group cannot guarantee any particular result. The Client acknowledges that <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> has made no promises about the outcome and that any opinion offered by <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> in the future will not constitute a guaranty. <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> is not liable for damages caused by advice or documents provided to the Client if they are used for any other purpose than that for which they were originally prepared. <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> is only liable to the party who entered into the Agreement with <strong>bf solution Group</strong> and will not accept liability for damage that may be caused to any third person.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 70%;">KNOW YOUR CUSTOMER AND VAT INFORMATION:</h3>
<p>Under the respective regulation on prevention of money laundering and terrorist financing, <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> must identify its client as well as persons acting on the Client’s behalf and the final beneficiaries of the Client.</p>
<p><strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may be obligated to decline or suspend an assignment and report to the authorities if the Client does not provide the required information, if a transaction is suspicious in comparison with previously known transactions, or if assets are suspected of being used for terrorist financing or money laundering. Although it is the professional and legal obligation of the <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> to avoid disclosing information concerning its Clients and the legal services provided to them, under the applicable mandatory regulation may require <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> to inform the authorities about cash transactions exceeding a statutory amount, regardless of whether the transaction is carried out as a single payment or as several linked payments, or if it becomes known to <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> or <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> has reason to suspect that any given transaction being carried out in the Client’s name may be related to money laundering</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 35%;">ENTIRE AGREEMENT:</h3>
<p>This agreement contains the entire agreement of the parties. No other agreement, statement, or promise made on or before the effective date of this agreement will be binding on the parties.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 40%;">FACSIMILE SIGNATURE:</h3>
<p>Client's facsimile signature on this agreement will constitute Client's original signature and Client's acceptance of the terms of this Agreement.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 65%;">MODIFICATION BY SUBSEQUENT AGREEMENT:</h3>
<p>This agreement may be modified by subsequent agreement of the parties only by an instrument in writing signed by both of them or an oral agreement to the extent that the parties carry it out.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 23%;">AMENDMENTS:</h3>
<p>The <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may unilaterally amend these General Terms and Conditions from time to time, notifying the Client by e-mail at least 30 calendar days in advance. Bf Solution Group publishes amendments to the General Terms and Conditions on its website <a href="https://bfsolution.group" style="color: #eb9637;">https://bfsolution.group</a> . The Client that does not agree with an amendment to the General Terms and Conditions may terminate the Agreement.</p>
<h3 style="color: #eb9637;background: #0c1a3c;padding: 5px; width: 49%;">EFFECTIVE DATE OF AGREEMENT:</h3>
<p>The effective date of this agreement will be the date when, having been executed by Client, the agreement is received by <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> . Once effective, this agreement will, however, apply to services provided by <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong>. on this matter before its effective date. Even if this agreement does not take effect, Client will be obligated to pay <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> the reasonable value of any services <strong>Bf Solution Group</strong> may have performed for Client.</p>
